{
  "text": "However, Crumpei and Dafinoiu investigated 77 medical workers from emergency and intensive care units including nurses and found no relationship between STS and empathy [CITATION_1] . Despite the facts that empathy in nurses is viewed to enhance the positive outcomes of provided care [CITATION_2] , this relationship needs further scrutiny because of its negative effect on the ED nurses. Being involved in high empathetic relationship with traumatized patients may transfer trauma feelings from the patient to nurses and consequently place them at risk for developing STS.",
